page.title: 14LOCAL NEWS OVER 100 YEARS(2)
page.content:
50 YEARS AGO (1935): JAN.15th.MRS.H.WILSON RAISED A TOTAL OF Â£10 4s 5d THROUGH THE 'WORN OUT WOOLIES' FUND. FEB 23rd.MR.J.DOWELL DIED AFTER MUCH SUFFERING.HE WAS A RESPECTED RESIDENT OF THE AREA FOR 69 YEARS. MARCH 9th.FOOTBALL RESULT FROM PROSPECT PARK,READING: SHINFIELD 0 READING 0
25 YEARS AGO (1960): JAN.15th.THE BRITISH LEGION CHILDRENS PARTY.70 CHILDREN ATTENDED AND AFTER THE R.E.M.E. BAND AND THE TRICK ARTISTS HAD PERFORMED,FATHER CHRISTMAS GAVE OUT PRESENTS. APRIL 29th.SHINFIELD EISTEDDFOD ENDED ON SATURDAY.ENTRIES WERE AGAIN DOWN,A FALL OF 70 ENTRIES FROM THE PREVIOUS YEAR.
